
# ğŸŒ Cisco BGP Protocol Configuration Guide

This README outlines a basic setup for BGP (Border Gateway Protocol) used in inter-domain routing.

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Basic Router Setup

```bash
enable
configure terminal
hostname ROUTER_NAME
no ip domain-lookup
```

---

## ğŸŒ Interface IP Configuration

```bash
interface FastEthernet0/0
  ip address 192.168.1.1 255.255.255.0
  no shutdown
exit
```

---

## ğŸ” BGP Configuration

```bash
router bgp 65001
  neighbor 192.168.1.2 remote-as 65002
  network 10.0.0.0 mask 255.255.255.0
exit
```

---

## ğŸ” Verification Commands

```bash
show ip bgp summary
show ip bgp
show running-config
```

---

## ğŸ’¾ Save Configuration

```bash
copy running-config startup-config
```

